    "stix_id": "indicator--4711a04ae9e56e624015fca814838852",
    "title": "Fedora Hummingbird brings the container security model to a Linux host OS",
    "description": "Container image security pipelines have spent the past several years pushing toward minimal footprints, hermetic builds, and continuous CVE remediation. The Fedora Project is now applying that same approach to the host operating system. At Red Hat Summit 2026, Fedora announced Fedora Hummingbird, a container-based rolling Linux distribution delivered as an OCI image. &#8220;The Linux market has split: IT operations teams need the decades-long stability of Red Hat Enterprise Linux, while builders",
