    "title": "CVE-2026-45185 - Exim GnuTLS Use-After-Free Remote Code Execution Vulnerability",
    "description": "CVE ID : CVE-2026-45185\n   \n   Published :  May 12, 2026, 8:16 p.m. | 37 minutes ago\n   \n   Description : Exim before 4.99.3, in certain GnuTLS configurations, has a remotely reachable use-after-free in the BDAT body parsing path. It is triggered when a client sends a TLS close_notify mid-body during a CHUNKING transfer, followed by a final cleartext byte on the same TCP connection. This can lead to heap corruption. An unauthenticated network attacker exploiting this vulnerability could execute",
